  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "To configure TCS mail on an iPhone, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Open iPhone Settings\n2. Select \"Mail\"\n3. Tap \"Accounts\"\n4. Choose \"Add Account\"\n5. Select \"Exchange\" or \"Other\" account type\n6. Enter your TCS email address\n7. Enter your email password\n8. Enter server details:\n   - Incoming mail server: Typically outlook.office365.com\n   - Outgoing mail server: smtp.office365.com\n9. Configure additional settings like SSL, ports\n10. Choose which services to sync (Mail, Contacts, Calendar)\n\nFor specific precise configuration, recommend:\n- Consulting TCS IT support\n- Checking official TCS email configuration guidelines\n- Verifying exact server settings with your specific TCS email account\n\nNote: Exact steps might vary slightly depending on your specific TCS email configuration and iPhone iOS version.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
